text.section:
A mortgage loan shall not be made or acquired by a domestic insurer unless an appraisal has been made by a competent appraiser for the purpose of the investment which meets the following requirements:
The appraisal shall be made prior to the date that the insurer commits to make the investment;
The appraisal shall be written and shall state an opinion of value as of a specific date, supported by presentation and analysis of relevant market material;
The appraisal shall provide the current fair market value of the real estate, that is the value of the real estate in an arms-length sale as of the date of the appraisal; and
The appraisal shall be reviewed and signed by a principal of the firm. The principal shall be a specific individual having appraisal experience with the property type, and shall be accountable for the conclusions contained in the report.
